para_trans: Regarding administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report (DPR) submitted by the local bodies for the works to be taken up out of the prize money received under Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0.
Dhakambe Gram Panchayat.
Government of Maharashtra
Department of Environment and Climate Change
Government Decision No: Mission-2024 / Q. No.04 (63) / T.C.9
Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Madam Cama Marg,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032
Date: 26th of May, 2025

Read: (1) Government Decision, Environment and Climate Change Department No. Mission - 2024 / Q. No.66 / T. 1 dated 27th September, 2024 (2) Government Decision, Department of Environment and Climate Change No. Abhiyaan-20219 / P.S. No.57 / T. No.1, dated 8th February, 2022 (3) The minutes of the meeting of the Committee constituted for the approval of the Administrator dated 02nd May, 2025
The Proposal:

The cash prizes to the winning local bodies in the 12 categories of Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 and the procedure for the appropriation of the prize money has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. (1). Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to give administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.
The government's decision:

Considering the points mentioned in the Preamble, the total amount received by the Dhakambe Gram Panchayat under My Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 is Rs. 50.00 The focus will be on the works to be undertaken out of the prize money of Rs. 50, 12, 980.00 (Rupees fifty lakhs twelve thousand nine hundred and eighty only) Detailed Project Report

Government Decision No: Mission-2024 / Q.No.04 / T.H.2, dated: 26th May, 2025

The Village Development Officer, Dhakambe Gram Panchayat has submitted it with the technical approval of the Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad Nashik. The proposal was submitted by the Dhakambe Gram Panchayat. The date of the Committee constituted under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change was taken into consideration in its meeting held on 02.05.2025. As per the recommendation made by the said Committee, the total amount submitted by the Dhakambe Gram Panchayat is Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing Rs.50, 12, 980.00 (Rupees fifty lakhs twelve thousand nine hundred UM only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions.
The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
2. Terms and Conditions:
1) The working mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report shall be the Gram Panchayat.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) Expenditure in excess of the prize money should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. Under the Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan, Dhakambe Gram Panchayat has been given a grant of Rs. A prize of ₹1 lakh has been received. Out of the prize money of Rs. The first instalment of ₹1 lakh has been disbursed to them. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been granted administrative approval by the Government as per paragraph-1 above, the balance of the prize money to the Dhakambe Gram Panchayat is Rs. The government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹1 lakh (₹TAA lakh only) through the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
